Name: Assets
Description: Resources owned by the business that have economic value

Name: Current Assets
Description: Assets expected to be converted to cash or used within one year

Name: Cash
Description: Money in bank accounts and cash on hand

Name: Accounts Receivable
Description: Money owed to the business by customers

Name: Inventory
Description: Goods available for sale or materials used in production

Name: Prepaid Expenses
Description: Expenses paid in advance such as insurance or rent

Name: Short-term Investments
Description: Investments expected to be converted to cash within one year

Name: Fixed Assets
Description: Long-term assets used in business operations

Name: Equipment
Description: Machinery and equipment used in operations

Name: Furniture and Fixtures
Description: Office furniture and permanent fixtures

Name: Buildings
Description: Structures owned by the business

Name: Land
Description: Real estate owned by the business

Name: Vehicles
Description: Cars, trucks, and other transportation equipment

Name: Accumulated Depreciation
Description: Total depreciation taken against fixed assets

Name: Other Assets
Description: Assets not classified as current or fixed

Name: Intangible Assets
Description: Non-physical assets like patents, trademarks, and goodwill

Name: Long-term Investments
Description: Investments held for more than one year

Name: Liabilities
Description: Obligations and debts owed by the business

Name: Current Liabilities
Description: Debts due within one year

Name: Accounts Payable
Description: Money owed to suppliers for goods or services purchased on credit

Name: Accrued Expenses
Description: Expenses incurred but not yet paid

Name: Payroll Liabilities
Description: Amounts owed to employees and tax authorities for payroll

Name: Short-term Loans
Description: Loans due within one year

Name: Current Portion of Long-term Debt
Description: Principal due within one year on long-term debt

Name: Unearned Revenue
Description: Payments received from customers before goods or services are delivered

Name: Sales Tax Payable
Description: Sales tax collected from customers but not yet paid to the government

Name: Long-term Liabilities
Description: Debts due beyond one year

Name: Mortgage Payable
Description: Long-term loans secured by real estate

Name: Notes Payable
Description: Formal written promises to pay specified amounts

Name: Bonds Payable
Description: Long-term debt securities issued by the business

Name: Equity
Description: Ownership interest in the business

Name: Owner's Equity
Description: Owner's investment in the business

Name: Capital
Description: Owner's contributions to the business

Name: Owner Draws
Description: Withdrawals of business assets for personal use

Name: Retained Earnings
Description: Accumulated profits reinvested in the business

Name: Common Stock
Description: Shares of ownership issued to stockholders

Name: Additional Paid-in Capital
Description: Amount paid by shareholders for stock in excess of par value

Name: Revenue
Description: Income earned from business activities

Name: Operating Revenue
Description: Income from primary business activities

Name: Service Revenue
Description: Income from services provided to customers

Name: Product Sales
Description: Income from selling goods to customers

Name: Other Revenue
Description: Income from secondary business activities

Name: Interest Income
Description: Income earned from investments or bank accounts

Name: Rental Income
Description: Income from renting property to others

Name: Gain on Sale of Assets
Description: Profits from selling business assets

Name: Expenses
Description: Costs incurred in business operations

Name: Cost of Goods Sold
Description: Direct costs of producing goods or services sold

Name: Purchases
Description: Cost of inventory bought for resale

Name: Direct Labor
Description: Wages paid to employees directly involved in production

Name: Manufacturing Overhead
Description: Indirect costs of production not easily traceable to specific products

Name: Operating Expenses
Description: Costs of running the business not directly tied to production

Name: Office Expenses
Description: Costs related to office operations

Name: Office Supplies
Description: Consumable items used in the office

Name: Office Equipment
Description: Small equipment items not capitalized

Name: Payroll Expenses
Description: All costs related to employee compensation

Name: Salaries and Wages
Description: Regular pay to employees

Name: Payroll Taxes
Description: Employer portion of taxes on employee wages

Name: Employee Benefits
Description: Health insurance, retirement plans, and other benefits

Name: Rent and Utilities
Description: Costs for business facilities

Name: Rent
Description: Payments for leased property

Name: Utilities
Description: Electricity, water, gas, internet, and phone services

Name: Professional Services
Description: Fees paid to outside service providers

Name: Legal Fees
Description: Costs for legal counsel and services

Name: Accounting Fees
Description: Costs for accounting and bookkeeping services

Name: Consulting Fees
Description: Payments to consultants and advisors

Name: Insurance
Description: Business insurance premiums

Name: Marketing and Advertising
Description: Costs to promote the business

Name: Travel and Entertainment
Description: Business travel, meals, and entertainment expenses

Name: Depreciation Expense
Description: Allocation of asset costs over their useful lives

Name: Other Expenses
Description: Expenses not classified elsewhere

Name: Interest Expense
Description: Interest paid on loans and credit

Name: Bank Fees
Description: Charges for banking services

Name: Loss on Sale of Assets
Description: Losses from selling business assets

Name: Income Taxes
Description: Taxes paid on business profits
